-- pd.package: FTD font_package package
name: athula10.github.io/font_package

This FTD font `font_package` package is for your ftd web projects. To Use this
font_package inside `FTD` project follow below instructions.

-- ds.h3: How to use font_package?

-- ds.code: Add this to your FASTN.ftd
lang: ftd

\-- fastn.dependency: athula10.github.io/font_package

-- ds.markdown: 

After adding font_package dependency inside your `FASTN.ftd` file, You need to
add font_package assets and import it inside your `.ftd` files where you are
using this font for your custom font types. 

To include font_package into your `ftd` file follow below instructions.

-- ds.code:
lang: ftd

\-- import: athula10.github.io/font_package/assets as font_package-assets


-- ds.h3: How to create a custom font_package type? 

-- ds.markdown: 

We don't recommend creating custom types. We recommend to use 
our [font_package-typography](https://athula10.github.io/font_package-typography)

If you're using [font_package-typography](https://athula10.github.io/font_package-typography) 
and still your designer has introduced new font size which are not included or 
part of our [font_package-typography](https://athula10.github.io/font_package-typography) 
then only define custom types. 

We hope you shouldn't need to define a custom type.

Below is an example of creating a custom `ftd.type` using font_package.

-- ds.rendered:

-- ds.rendered.input:

\-- ftd.type font_package-size-12-desktop:
size.px: 12
weight: 400
font-family: $font_package-assets.fonts.<font-name>


\-- ftd.type font_package-size-12-mobile:
size.px: 12
weight: 400
font-family: $font_package-assets.fonts.<font-name>

\-- ftd.responsive-type font_package-size-12-400:
desktop: $font_package-size-12-desktop
mobile: $font_package-size-12-mobile

\-- ftd.text: 
role: $font_package-size-12-400
color: $inherited.colors.text-strong

`font-size: 12px, font-weight: 400` 

üëâ The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog 

